devdoc.details: This contract is basically my life organized on the blockchain. It's a todo list for a 21-year-old navigating life, code, and vibes. It allows adding, updating, and managing daily tasks on the blockchain.

addTodo(string).details: Adds a new task to the list. Public facing function.

params._content: The description of the task. Cannot be an empty string.

constructor.details: Constructor: Contract created! Let's pre-fill some realistic tasks. This is where the daily grind gets listed.

deleteTodo(uint256).details: Marks a todo as deleted. On blockchain, we usually mark instead of truly deleting.

params._id: The ID of the task to delete.

getAllTodoIds().details: Gets all the todo IDs. Useful for frontends to iterate through tasks.

returns._0: An array of all todo IDs.

getAllTodos().details: Gets all todo items. This iterates through all IDs and fetches each todo. Note: This can be gas-intensive for a very large number of todos.

returns._0: An array of all Todo structs.

getTodo(uint256).details: Gets the details of a specific task.

params._id: The ID of the task to retrieve.

returns.isDeleted: Whether the task is marked as deleted.
returns.status: The current status of the task.

getTotalTodos().details: Gets the total number of tasks in the list (including deleted ones).

returns._0: The total count of tasks added.

updateContent(uint256,string).details: Updates the content of a task. Need to rephrase something?

params._id: The ID of the task to update.
params._newContent: The new description of the task. Cannot be an empty string.

updateStatus(uint256,uint8).details: Updates the status of a task. Did I finish it? Am I working on it?

params._id: The ID of the task to update.
params._status: The new status (Pending, InProgress, Completed, Deleted).
